          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "I have lost count of how many times I landed in a new country, opened my phone, and felt that sinking realization: no signal, no Wi-Fi, and a taxi driver expecting me to navigate with Google Maps. Traditional roaming charges are absurd — I once paid $15 for a single day of slow data in Japan. That experience alone sent me searching for something better.",
