        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h2",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "What Is eSIMania and Why Does It Matter?",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [
          {
            "_key": "l1",
            "_type": "link",
            "href": "https://tonyciencia.com/en/posts/what-is-esimania"
          }
        ],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "eSIMania",
            "marks": [
              "l1"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " is a platform that sells eSIMs — digital SIM cards you install directly on your phone — for international travel. Instead of hunting for a physical SIM card kiosk at the airport or paying your carrier's roaming fees, you buy a plan online, scan a QR code, and you are connected in minutes.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "The platform covers over 200 countries, offers data-only plans with varying data caps and validity windows, and has a cashback and referral rewards system baked in. It launched in 2023 and has quickly built a reputation for simplicity and fair pricing.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "If you have never used an eSIM before, think of it as a SIM card that lives inside your phone's chip. Most modern iPhones (XS and later), Google Pixels, Samsung Galaxy S20+, and many other devices support them. No physical card. No tools. No store visits.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [
          {
