      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "This is the scenario that made me a believer. Last spring, I spent three weeks hopping between France, Germany, Italy, and Spain. In the past, that meant buying a new prepaid SIM in each country — four separate purchases, four phone numbers, four sets of instructions.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "With eSIMania, I bought a plan covering the region before I even left home. I scanned the QR code at Charles de Gaulle airport in Paris, and the same data plan worked seamlessly as I took the train to Berlin, then Rome, then Barcelona.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Why this works so well:",
